:::'''Damionis:''' Ah, esteemed outlander. Your timing is impeccable. I, Damionis, have recently made yet another significant discovery.
::<!--Ends the current performance-->
::<!--Open NPC Menu-->
:;(If {{cx}}<!--SubMission Started: 803010101-->)
:{{DIcon|undefined}} I heard that you're currently working on some kind of plan?
:::<!--Trigger PerformanceE 803010101: Config/Level/Mission/8030101/Act/Act803010101.json-->
:::'''Damionis:''' Where did you... Ahem... I mean, you're right!
:::'''Damionis:''' I, Damionis, have discovered a superb business opportunity lying just outside the walls of the holy city.
:::'''Damionis:''' Do you want to join in, hero? If we get our hands on it, we will surely become the trailblazers of the new era! Great fortune is awaiting us!
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Hmph, you got me in hot soup last time!
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_830110105-->
::::'''Damionis:''' Aye, can you really blame me...? I was just too excited back then. But no one's getting into hot soup this time, because adventuring is what I do!
::::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_830110109-->
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} You're actually interested in making money?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_830110107-->
::::'''Damionis:''' ...Ehehe. Well, I do yearn for the skies, but I should also occasionally have to turn my face back down to earth.
::::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_830110109-->
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Give me more details first.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_830110109-->
:::'''Damionis:''' I hear you're from a world beyond the sky, so you might not know this... But the holy city used to span across far greater lands than what you see now.
:::'''Damionis:''' A long time ago, countless allied cities existed around Okhema... In the same way that Oronyx's stars surround the Dawn Device.
:::'''Damionis:''' Okhema was a true "Eternal City" back then. People did not think of it as their city, but rather a motherly figure. When one stood on top of the hill and looked outward, everything we could see was our territory!
:::'''Damionis:''' ...Then, the black tide raged stronger. The area within the city walls became the only safe place, while all other regions gradually grew deserted.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} How tragic...
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_830110114-->
::::'''Damionis:''' ...Isn't it? But it's also thanks to these events of the past that we have an opportunity to strike it rich.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Why were they deserted?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_830110116-->
::::'''Damionis:''' Rather than protecting such a vast territory, isn't it more feasible to fall back and defend just the city walls? But I guess it's also thanks to these events of the past that we have an opportunity to strike it rich.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Are we going to... go grave digging?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_830110118-->
::::'''Damionis:''' Err, you're not entirely wrong. I am more inclined to think that we're going to bring back items that still have worth.
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_830110119-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_830110119-->
:::'''Damionis:''' When Nikador was still active, everything beyond the walls of the holy city was living under the mad king's shadow. Their giant spear even sent some states buried several feet into the ground... We're not going to reach those places for sure.
:::'''Damionis:''' His titankins are beginning to die down now that you've defeated the mad king, making this the perfect time to go on an adventure!
:::'''Damionis:''' The ancient cities may be in utter ruin by now, but I'm sure some parts of them managed to remain as they were... Say, places that have been buried underground.
:::'''Damionis:''' I found an underground palace beneath an ancient hypogeum around here a while ago. Just dig up those treasures, and you can stay however long you want in the holy city... Heck, you can even buy whatever you want here!
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Are they really worth that much?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_830110124-->
::::'''Damionis:''' How does that saying go again? Ah, "the most valuable things are all buried underground." Along with a ton of traps and danger, of course...
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Are you sure it'll be safe?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_830110126-->
::::'''Damionis:''' I've checked out the site a dozen times now and I haven't seen a single monster! ...Maybe except for a few of their defense mechanisms that are still functioning.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} What's a hypogeum?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_830110128-->
::::'''Damionis:''' A massive underground building complex that was likely used as a vault to store valuable items... and safeguarded with defense mechanisms that may be still functioning.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I'm not interested in money.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_830110130-->
::::'''Damionis:''' ...But you'll at least receive glory. I mean, think about your potential title &mdash; "Reclaimer of Lost Lands"! Isn't that a noble title to be known by?
::::'''Damionis:''' As for proof? The treasures that you bring back will make for the most irrefutable proof. As long as you bring back a large enough pile of treasures, the rest will be convinced of your incredible feat.
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_830110132-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_830110132-->
:::'''Damionis:''' In any case, our plan is simple: I'll lead the way, and you can sort out whatever mechanisms that remain. And when we finally get to the treasures, we can split them 3-7.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Why am I only getting 70% of the treasures?
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} You're only taking 30% of the treasures? Don't you want more?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_830110135-->
:::'''Damionis:''' Huh? I'm getting 70%. The 30% is yours.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} You have a chance to reconsider your words.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I'm not going then.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_830110138-->
:::'''Damionis:''' ...Oh, alright. I'll admit that we can't do this without you... but the same goes for me.
:::'''Damionis:''' Let's both compromise and agree on an equal split?
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Fine.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_830110141-->
::::'''Damionis:''' Excellent. That's why I like working with people like you.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Not okay.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_830110143-->
::::'''Damionis:''' Bah, I'll just live with a 7-3 split... This is final! No more negotiation on how we're splitting the loot!
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Negotiate any further and it'll be a 9-1 split.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_830110145-->
