::{{DIcon}} Can you tell me what you've discovered?
:::'''Damionis:''' I've been stationed at the base of Kephale from Entry Hour to Curtain-Fall Hour, fasting and unblinking, until at last... I've unraveled the mysteries of the Dawn Device!
:::'''Damionis:''' That is &mdash; the light emitted by the Dawn Device is not constant. When observed through the highest precision lenses, one can detect extremely subtle fluctuations in brightness. Although these changes are not readily apparent, they are indeed real and measurable.
:::'''Damionis:''' This indicates that the traditional method of timekeeping is utterly unsuitable for modern Okhema!
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: waitoption_damiyanuosi-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: waitoption_damiyanuosi-->
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} Aren't you an explorer?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504038201-->
::::'''Damionis:''' Isn't delving into the unknown secrets of Okhema an exhilarating adventure?
::::'''Damionis:''' Well, actually, I had sworn in front of Lady Aglaea not to try to explore the world beyond the sky. I need to keep up appearances, at least for the time being.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} What a great discovery!
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504038204-->
::::'''Damionis:''' Exactly! By sharing this discovery, we could revolutionize the longstanding calendar system in Okhema!
::::'''Damionis:''' Imagine this &mdash; the five periods of the day, established by Kephale in ancient times and widely recognized ever since are now proven to need modification. What a startling discovery!
::::'''Damionis:''' I should jot this down quickly &mdash; wouldn't want to let it slip my mind.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} ...I don't understand what you mean.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504038208-->
::::'''Damionis:''' ...Is this so hard to grasp? Never mind, let me explain it in detail.
::::'''Damionis:''' Okhema adheres to a traditional calendar, dividing each day into five distinct periods based on the mistaken belief that the light from the Dawn Device remains constant and cannot be used to determine time.
::::'''Damionis:''' But I have proven that the light from the Dawn Device does indeed change. Could we then base a new calendar on this discovery? Am I, Damionis, actually correcting Kephale's original creation?
::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} That's incredible!
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504038213-->
:::::'''Damionis:''' Thank you, thank you. The spirit of exploration deserves praise. Praise my free, unbound soul!
::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} But Okhema does not need a new calendar.
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504038215-->
:::::'''Damionis:''' Be that as it may, I know people are accustomed to this method of timekeeping and are not keen on any changes, but...
:::::'''Damionis:''' As an explorer, I'm driven to seek the unknown! Even if it yields no practical results, I'm determined to prove that my conjectures are correct!
::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Exit}} So what do you plan to do?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504038217-->
::::'''Damionis:''' I will go to the Council of Elders with my conjectures and invite Grove scholars to witness my findings. I'll give lectures in the marketplace, and hold discussions in the baths. I want everyone to know about this.
::::'''Damionis:''' Sharing exciting discoveries is the first step toward change &mdash; wish me luck, esteemed outlander!
